    "faq": [
      {
        "question": "Does this skill work with GitLab or other platforms?",
        "answer": "This skill is designed for GitHub using the gh CLI. Other platforms are not supported at this time."
      },
      {
        "question": "What git commands does this skill use?",
        "answer": "It uses git log, git diff, and git status to gather changes, plus gh pr commands for GitHub operations."
      },
      {
        "question": "Can I customize the output format?",
        "answer": "Yes, the skill follows best practices but can be customized based on your team's PR template requirements."
      },
      {
        "question": "Is my code or repository data sent anywhere?",
        "answer": "No. All git operations run locally. Only PR creation/update calls are made to GitHub's official API."
      },
      {
        "question": "What if my PR has no changes to commit?",
        "answer": "The skill will note that no changes are detected. Ensure you have staged or committed your changes first."
      },
      {
        "question": "How is this different from GitHub's PR template feature?",
        "answer": "This skill actively generates content based on your actual code changes, filling in details automatically rather than just prompting for input."
